{"timestamp": "2025-12-06 10:35:00.630586", "event": "llm_end", "text": "Submitted.\n\nSummary:\n- Anomaly: Yes\n- Faulty device(s): dns_server (10.200.0.2)\n- Root cause: dns_record_error\n\nRationale:\n- BIND/named is running and listening on 53/udp,tcp, but queries time out locally and remotely.\n- No authoritative zone exists for the local enterprise domain (web*.local), and no forwarders are configured; in an environment without public DNS reachability, recursion stalls, causing timeouts.\n- Result: All hostname-based access (e.g., web99.local, web0.local) fails, while access by IP works.", "generation_info": {"finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 2283, "output_tokens": 131, "total_tokens": 2414, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 0}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 0}}}
